            <div type="translation">
                <p xml:lang="en">
                    <persName ref="#oppius_marinus" xml:lang="la">Oppius Marinus</persName> purchased for himself, at his own expense, a chest and ordered that it be inscribed: if after his death any outsider wished to place themselves in it, they should pay six roman pound of silver to the <term xml:lang="la">fiscus</term>.
                </p>
                <p xml:lang="it">
                    <persName ref="#oppius_marinus" xml:lang="la">Oppius Marinus</persName> acquistò per sé, con il proprio lavoro, un'arca e ordinò che fosse scritto: se dopo la sua morte qualcuno estraneo volesse collocarsi in essa, versi al <term xml:lang="la">fiscus</term> sei libbre d'argento.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                    <p>The <term xml:lang="la">gens</term> <persName xml:lang="la">Oppia</persName> (<term xml:lang="la">CIL</term> V 8689; <ref target="http://www.edr-edr.it/edr_programmi/res_complex_comune.php?do=book&amp;id_nr=EDR097849">EDR097849</ref>) and the <term xml:lang="la">cognomen</term> <persName xml:lang="la">Marinus</persName> (<term xml:lang="la">CIL</term> V 1918; <ref target="http://www.edr-edr.it/edr_programmi/res_complex_comune.php?do=book&amp;id_nr=EDR097787">EDR097787</ref>) are already attested in Concordia as early as the Early Imperial period.</p>
                </div>
                <div type="commentary" xml:lang="it">
                    <p>La <term xml:lang="la">gens</term> <persName xml:lang="la">Oppia</persName> (<term xml:lang="la">CIL</term> V 8689; <ref target="http://www.edr-edr.it/edr_programmi/res_complex_comune.php?do=book&amp;id_nr=EDR097849">EDR097849</ref>) e il <term xml:lang="la">cognomen</term> <persName xml:lang="la">Marinus</persName> (<term xml:lang="la">CIL</term> V 1918; <ref target="http://www.edr-edr.it/edr_programmi/res_complex_comune.php?do=book&amp;id_nr=EDR097787">EDR097787</ref>) sono attestati a Concordia già in età alto imperiale.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
